Lecture 1: Introduction to Civics & Active Citizenship. Civics is the study of the rights and duties of citizenship. An active citizen is someone who takes an active role in their community, society, and nation. The core values of active citizenship include responsibility, respect, tolerance, and civic participation. Civic engagement refers to the ways in which citizens participate in the life of a community in order to improve conditions for others or to help shape the community's future. Forms of civic engagement include voting, volunteering, community organizing, and participating in local government.